===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|flour|lang=enm||flower}} from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|flor}} from {{etyl|la}} {{term|florem|flōrem|lang=la}}, accusative of {{term|flos|flōs|lang=la||flower}} from {{proto|Indo-European|bhlo-|to blossom, flourish|lang=}}, extended form of {{proto|Indo-European|bhel-|to thrive, bloom|lang=}}. Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[blede#Middle English|blede]]'' "flower" (from {{ang}} ''[[bled#Old English|blēd]]'' "flower, fruit"), {{enm}} ''[[blome#Middle English|blome]]'' "flower" (from {{non}} ''[[blomi#Old Norse|blōmi]]'' "flower"), {{enm}} ''[[blossem#Middle English|blosme, blossem]]'' "flower, blossom" (from {{ang}} ''[[blostma#Old English|blōstma]]'' "flower").

